    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is not a bug, `np.argsort` returns an indexer (i.e. which element should be in that position) not a rank.  You probably want something like the `rank` SO answer.\n\n``` python\nranks = df.rank(axis=1).astype(int)-1\n\nnew_values = df.columns.values.take(ranks)\n\npd.DataFrame(new_values)\nOut[101]: \n   0  1  2  3  4\n0  B  A  C  E  D\n1  A  E  D  C  B\n2  E  B  C  D  A\n3  B  C  D  E  A\n\n```\n"
